# Adv. DQL - Lab 3 - **Instructor Copy**

## Parsing and Relationships
---

### 3.1 Simple Parse: 

One of your colleagues has come to you with the following DQL, all they want to do is chart the amount of records by different instruments, they also want to exclude any data for IDs greater than 3 as they are not business critical, but their below DQL does not seem to work.

**Task**:

- Fix the below code so that you can chart the count of the different instruments over time

input.value:
fetch logs
| fields content
| filter contains(content,  "msg=\"Getting pricing data for instrument\"")
| parse content, """DATA "=\"" ISO8601:Time "\"" LD  " instrumentId=" INT:InstrumentId DATA"""
| filter InstrumentId <= 3
|  makeTimeseries count(), time:Time , by:{InstrumentId}

| filter InstrumentId <= 3
| makeTimeseries by:{InstrumentId}, time:Time, count()

### 3.2 Parsing and data types: 

Now that we are familiar with the dataset parse the log content to extract as many fields as you possible can from the records.

**Task**:

- Parse the below content to extract as much of the available information as you can
- *Challange*: for each of the extracted propertied ensure that you use a **different** parsing data type

input.value:
fetch logs
| fields content
| filter contains(content,  "msg=\"Getting pricing data for instrument\"") AND contains(content , "dt.span_id=")
| parse content, """DATA "=\"" ISO8601:Time "\"" LD "level=" WORD:LogLevel " msg=" CSVDQS:Message " dt.span_id=" ALNUM:DTSpan " dt.trace_id=" LD:DTTraceId " dt.trace_sampled=" BOOLEAN:Sampled " instrumentId=" INT:InstrumentId " records=" LONG:Records"""
| fieldsRemove  content
| limit 100
